The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 12 September is 3,164 (366.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 08 September, there were 153 new confirmed cases (17.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 01 September, there were 53 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 189% (100 extra cases).
